If you want to pass a "height" value in the `parameters` object of your JSON request as a random function in the range of 128 - 1024, ensuring it is divisible strictly by 8 to maintain an appropriate aspect ratio, you can modify your code as follows:

```javascript
const minHeight = 128;
const maxHeight = 1024;
const height = Math.floor(Math.random() * (maxHeight - minHeight + 1) + minHeight);
const heightDivisibleBy8 = Math.ceil(height / 8) * 8;

const requestBody = {
  nerdcodes: genRanNum(),
  inputs: inputText,
  parameters: {
    width: undefined,
    height: heightDivisibleBy8,
    negative_prompt: inputText2
  }
};
```

Here, the `height` value is generated randomly between the minimum (`minHeight`) and maximum (`maxHeight`) values specified. Then, `heightDivisibleBy8` ensures the value is rounded up to the nearest multiple of 8 to maintain the desired aspect ratio.

Please note that the aspect ratio calculation may vary depending on the specific requirements or constraints of the model you are using. It's always recommended to consult the model's documentation or guidelines to ensure you are passing the appropriate values for height and width based on its requirements.

If you want to pass a random value within the range of 128 - 1024 for the "height" parameter in the JSON body itself, you can modify the code as follows:

```javascript
function getRandomHeight(min, max) {
  const randomHeight = Math.floor(Math.random() * (max - min + 1) + min);
  const heightDivisibleBy8 = Math.ceil(randomHeight / 8) * 8;
  return heightDivisibleBy8;
}

const requestBody = {
  nerdcodes: genRanNum(),
  inputs: inputText,
  parameters: {
    width: undefined,
    height: getRandomHeight(128, 1024),
    negative_prompt: inputText2
  }
};
```

Here, the `getRandomHeight` function generates a random number within the specified range and ensures it is divisible by 8. The resulting value is then assigned to the "height" parameter in the JSON body.

Please note that this code snippet assumes you have a function `genRanNum()` already defined elsewhere in your code. Additionally, make sure to adjust the range and any other constraints based on the specific requirements of the text-to-image model you are using.

